SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 665
By Reeves
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Jim Tracy for his
exemplary service to the State of Tennessee
and his fellow citizens.
WHEREAS, Jim Tracy has proven himself to be a noble public servant throughout his
many endeavors in the local, state, and federal levels of government; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Tracy was a valuable member of the Tennessee Senate for thirteen
years (2005-2017) before resigning to serve in President Donald J. Trump's first administration
as State Director of United States Department of Agriculture (USDA) Rural Development for
Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, he established lifelong ties to agriculture and the land while growing up in
West Tennessee, where his father was a county extension agent; Mr. Tracy was active in 4-H
and on the family farm as a youth, and he later taught agricultural education at the high school
level; and
WHEREAS, as USDA State Director, Mr. Tracy used his real-life agricultural experience,
legislative skills, and good judgment "to oversee rural development programs in a customer-
focused manner to restore prosperity in rural Tennessee"; and
WHEREAS, a strong advocate for rural and agriculture issues during his time in the
Senate, he chaired the body's Transportation and Safety Committee, served as Speaker Pro
Tempore, and was a member of the Commerce and Labor and Education committees; and
WHEREAS, in 2007, he astutely guided to passage landmark legislation that prohibited
smoking in public indoor places, state facilities, and places of employment, a great
accomplishment that helped improve the health of Tennesseans; and
WHEREAS, during his tenure in the General Assembly, Senator Tracy worked with
purpose and conviction to cut taxes, reduce spending, and make Tennessee State government
SJR0665
012378
- 1 -

more transparent and efficient, while providing sound leadership on legislative issues vital to his
constituents and the State as a whole; and
WHEREAS, prior to his service in the Senate, Jim Tracy was a highly influential figure in
his community, serving on the Bedford County's Board of Education, Chamber of Commerce,
and Economic Development and Tourism Committee; and
WHEREAS, in January 2021, Mr. Tracy returned to State government when he was
appointed by Governor Bill Lee as a senior advisor for the Department of Commerce and
Insurance; and
WHEREAS, a graduate of the University of Tennessee at Martin, Jim Tracy operated his
own small business for twenty-four years, working as an insurance agent, and was a highly
regarded NCAA basketball official for ten years; and
WHEREAS, throughout his career, Jim Tracy has demonstrated the positive difference
one person can make in a community through dedication and diligence; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Tracy is a man of integrity who has never sacrificed his values for
expediency, and we would do well to follow his example of courage and compassion in public
service; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Jim Tracy for his
exemplary service to the State of Tennessee and his fellow citizens and extend to him our best
wishes for much continued success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
